  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>A sudden loud ringing noise, painfully intense, erupts from a point of your choice within range. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} centered on that point must make a &amp;Reference[con]{Constitution} saving throw. A creature takes 3d8 &amp;Reference[thunder]{thunder} damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A creature made of inorganic &amp;Reference[material]{material} such as stone, crystal, or metal has disadvantage on this saving throw.</p>\n<p>A nonmagical object that isn't being worn or carried also takes the damage if it's in the spell's area.</p>\n<p><strong>At Higher Levels. </strong>When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 2nd.</p>\n</div>",
